{{Quote|What are they doing here? There's nothing important in this sector.''"<br />"''I've plotted the fleet's trajectory. They're headed for Rhen Var, in the Nabali system. If we hurry, we can get there first.|[[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]]|<ref name="Game">[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (video game)|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars'' video game]]</ref>}}
The '''Tobali system''', also known as the '''Nabali system''', was a [[Star system/Legends|system]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]] that contained the terrestrial [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Rhen Var/Legends|Rhen Var]]. It had two other planets in its orbit, both being gas giants. The two planets' orbits were located on the far side of an asteroid belt named Bardo Verwen, a belt possibly the remains of a planet.

==History==
The Tobali system was included in the [[Thanium sector/Legends|Thanium Worlds]], one of the feuding states that rose around 24,995 BBY from the remainder of Xim the Despot's empire, a century after his death. In 22 BBY, one month into the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] were on patrol in the Tobali system when they encountered a [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] fleet heading for the planet [[Rhen Var/Legends|Rhen Var]], where a small Republic supply base and listening post was set up. The system was conquered by the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] during the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].

